  "prompt": "What is process of hiring from Europe for foreign nationals?",
  "response": "Hiring from Europe for foreign nationals involves several steps and considerations:\n\n1. Work Permit/Visa Requirements\n- Obtain necessary work permits\n- Comply with EU immigration regulations\n- Understand specific country's work visa rules\n\n2. Recruitment Process\n- Post job advertisements on European job portals\n- Use international recruitment agencies\n- Conduct online interviews\n- Verify candidate qualifications and credentials\n\n3. Legal Considerations\n- Understand employment laws in specific European country\n- Comply with local labor regulations\n- Prepare employment contracts meeting local standards\n\n4. Documentation\n- Verify candidate's right to work\n- Collect necessary identification documents\n- Prepare work permit applications\n- Ensure passport and visa requirements are met\n\n5. Sponsorship Options\n- Company sponsorship\n- EU work permit sponsorship\n- Intra-company transfer programs\n- Professional employment organizations (PEOs)\n\n6. Compensation and Benefits\n- Research local salary standards\n- Understand taxation requirements\n- Provide competitive compensation packages\n- Consider relocation assistance\n\n7. Compliance\n- Follow EU employment regulations\n- Adhere to non-discrimination laws\n- Meet social security and healthcare requirements\n\n8. Onboarding\n- Provide cultural orientation\n- Assist with relocation logistics\n- Support integration into workplace\n\nEach European country has unique requirements, so specific processes may vary.",
